As the volume and complexity of financial text increased, researchers explored machine‑learning techniques—including SVMs, Random Forests, Gradient Boosting (e.g., XGBoost), and early neural networks—to improve predictive performance. While these algorithms capture nonlinearities better than classical statistical models, they still require extensive feature engineering, domain‑specific preprocessing, and manual interventions to extract meaningful patterns from text.

