3.2.1 Prompt‑Based LLMs and Zero‑Shot/Few‑Shot Adaptation
Early applications of LLMs in credit‑risk assessment leveraged prompt‑based learning, where models such as GPT variants interpret text and classify risk under zero‑shot or few‑shot paradigms. These methods bypass large‑scale domain-specific training and rely instead on optimized prompt engineering to guide the model’s reasoning.

