A second major branch of research focuses on fine‑tuning LLMs using domain‑specific financial datasets. Fine‑tuning enhances performance on specialised tasks—such as credit default prediction, risk scoring, or generating interpretative risk reports—by aligning the base model’s representations with domain‑specific semantics.

