Likewise, the systematic XAI review by Černevičienė and Kabašinskas (2024) confirms that SHAP, LIME, rule‑based methods, and hybrid frameworks dominate explainable financial AI. They find that XAI adoption is highest in credit management, fraud detection, and stock prediction—domains structurally similar to credit‑risk modelling. Furthermore, they note a growing trend toward multi‑method XAI frameworks, where multiple interpretability tools operate in tandem to produce more comprehensive explanations.
