1. Token‑Level vs Feature‑Level Interpretability
LLMs operate on token embeddings and contextual attention mechanisms rather than tabular features. As Golec & AlabdulJalil (2025) note, LLM‑specific interpretability must address not only which features or tokens mattered, but why particular semantic patterns or attention heads influenced predictions—a fundamentally different explanatory target.
