(c) Hybrid Structured + Unstructured Pipelines
Studies show that LLM‑generated or LLM‑processed text can meaningfully improve risk prediction when fused with structured borrower attributes.

Despite their strengths, LLM‑driven models remain constrained by monolingual training data, lack of compliance integration, limited cross‑lingual evaluation, and insufficient real‑time inference capacity.

