3.5.2 Multilingual Strategies (Innovations)
T3L (Translate‑and‑Test):
For non‑English inputs, use high‑quality NMT to English, but backpropagate through a “soft translation” layer during fine‑tuning to align translation and classifier.
Compare vs native multilingual encoders (XLM‑R) and language‑adaptive fine‑tuning (LoRA adapters per language).
Language‑Adaptive Fine‑Tuning (LAFT):
Add LoRA/IA³ adapters per language; freeze the base model to reduce compute and enable language‑specific specialization.
Use contrastive objectives to pull semantically equivalent finance terms across languages closer in embedding space.
